	     In this week's episode – former intelligence minister Ronnie Kasrils says President Jacob Zuma is a two-faced Judas who has betrayed his country. LISTEN. "As we later saw with money, he has such an unrelenting predator type approach," Kasrils said of President Zuma, following the launch of his book A Simple Man. Kasrils added that he asked former president Thabo Mbeki to contest for the role of ANC president in the lead up to the party's Polokwane conference, in an attempt to stop President Jacob Zuma from taking over the position. News24 politics editor Mahlatse Mahlase also speaks to ANC secretary general Gwede Mantashe - who said the conference will go ahead despite concerns over the litany of disputes from branch nomination meetings. Once you've listened, share the podcast with your circle and let us know what you think by voting in the poll below. POLOTIKI, a weekly politics podcast from News24. Listen on iTunes here.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  